## file.watch — event-driven file watcher

Use `file.watch` to **watch files or directories for changes** and react to them. This enables proactive AI workflows: "when X file changes, do Y".

**Use cases:**
- Watch a file edited by Windsurf/Cursor → auto-post to Jira/Linear/Slack
- Watch a log file → alert when error pattern appears
- Watch build output → notify when done
- Watch config file → trigger dependent action
- Watch any file and poll for changes before continuing a plan

**Actions:**
- `start` — begin watching a file or directory, returns `watchId`
- `stop` — stop a watcher by `watchId`
- `list` — list all active watchers and their recent events
- `poll` — check if a watched file has changed (optionally wait up to `pollTimeoutMs`)
- `read` — read current content of a watched file (with change metadata)

**Args:**
- `action` — required. One of: `start` | `stop` | `list` | `poll` | `read`
- `path` — file or directory to watch (required for `start`)
- `watchId` — watcher ID returned by `start` (required for `stop`/`poll`/`read`)
- `label` — human-readable name for this watcher (shown in list)
- `debounceMs` — debounce window to batch rapid events (default 500ms)
- `recursive` — watch directory and all subdirectories (default false)
- `pattern` — regex to filter which files trigger events (e.g. `"\\.js$"`)
- `pollTimeoutMs` — for `poll`: max ms to wait for a change before returning (default 0 = instant)

**Typical pattern — watch then poll:**
```
file.watch start → (other steps) → file.watch poll → synthesize/act on result
```

**Example — "Watch my Windsurf project for changes, then post to Jira when a file is saved":**
```json
[
  { "skill": "file.watch", "args": { "action": "start", "path": "~/Desktop/projects/myapp/src", "recursive": true, "label": "myapp src", "pattern": "\\.tsx?$" }, "description": "Start watching src directory for TypeScript file changes" },
  { "skill": "file.watch", "args": { "action": "poll", "watchId": "{{prev_watchId}}", "pollTimeoutMs": 300000 }, "description": "Wait up to 5 minutes for a file change" },
  { "skill": "browser.act", "args": { "action": "waitForAuth", "url": "https://your-org.atlassian.net", "profile": "jira", "authSuccessUrl": "atlassian.net", "sessionId": "jira1" }, "description": "Open Jira" },
  { "skill": "synthesize", "args": { "prompt": "Write a Jira comment saying: 'Code change detected in src/ — file updated. Ready for review.'" }, "description": "Draft Jira comment" }
]
```

**Example — "Watch my app.log for errors":**
```json
[
  { "skill": "file.watch", "args": { "action": "start", "path": "~/Desktop/projects/myapp/logs/app.log", "label": "app log" }, "description": "Start watching app.log" },
  { "skill": "file.watch", "args": { "action": "poll", "watchId": "{{prev_watchId}}", "pollTimeoutMs": 60000 }, "description": "Wait up to 1 minute for log changes" },
  { "skill": "file.watch", "args": { "action": "read", "watchId": "{{prev_watchId}}" }, "description": "Read current log content" },
  { "skill": "synthesize", "args": { "prompt": "Scan this log content for errors, warnings, or crashes. Summarize any issues found." }, "description": "Analyze log for issues" }
]
```

**Example — "List all active watchers":**
```json
[
  { "skill": "file.watch", "args": { "action": "list" }, "description": "List all active file watchers" }
]
```

**Note on `{{prev_watchId}}`:** The `watchId` from a `file.watch start` step is available as `{{prev_watchId}}` in subsequent steps — or you can use the explicit `watchId` string returned in the result.

